  m_Name: Wall Cabinet
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Wall Cabinet
  description: Wall cabinets in parlors were used to store valuable or personal items
    such as letters, drinking accessories, or small heirlooms. These cabinets were
    typically locked and only opened during social gatherings or by the head of the
    household. They were both practical storage and a way to keep important possessions
    on display but protected.
